Added the static docs deployment workflow in `.github/workflows/docs.yml`.

Manual review confirmed the workflow now:

- builds the docs site on pull requests, pushes to `main`, and manual dispatch
- uploads the built site as a workflow artifact
- deploys on `main` only when `TRANSIT_DOCS_DEPLOY_ENABLED=true`, or on manual dispatch with `deploy=true`
- syncs `website/build/` to S3
- issues a CloudFront invalidation
- reads deployment configuration from repository variables

Documented the deployment inputs in `website/README.md`:

- `TRANSIT_DOCS_DEPLOY_ENABLED`
- `TRANSIT_DOCS_SITE_URL`
- `TRANSIT_DOCS_BASE_URL`
- `TRANSIT_DOCS_BUCKET`
- `TRANSIT_DOCS_DISTRIBUTION_ID`
- `TRANSIT_DOCS_AWS_ROLE_ARN`
- `TRANSIT_DOCS_AWS_REGION`
